# m6_p09_wind_ice.shot — M6 P09
#
# Verifies the M6 P09 WIND + ICE compound. Setup:
#   - 20-tile-wide ICE strip at row 35 of Concourse (x=960..1600).
#   - A WIND ambient zone covering the same area, blowing RIGHT
#     (dir=(1,0)) at strength 1.0 (max wind = 250 px/s).
#   - Mech spawns at the LEFT edge of the ice; no player input.
#
# Expected: the WIND drives the mech RIGHT across the ICE strip
# without any input. On non-ice ground the WIND would barely budge
# the mech (contact friction 0.92 swamps it); on ICE (friction 1.0 +
# integrate damp 0.9995) the wind cleanly drives to ~250 px/s.

window 1920 1080
seed   42 42
out    build/shots/m6_p09_wind_ice

map concourse

# ICE strip — 20 tiles wide.
paint_rect 30 35 50 36 0x03

# WIND zone covering the ICE strip + a bit of clearance above so the
# spawn lands inside. Blowing east at strength 1.0.
# Rect: world (960, 992) → (1600, 1152). Wind dir (1, 0) = +X.
paint_ambi 0 960 992 1600 1152 1.0 1.0 0.0

# Spawn at left edge of the ice; high enough that the mech falls
# into the WIND zone.
spawn_at 1024 1000
mouse    1600 540

# Captures across ~6 seconds. No input — the mech should DRIFT right
# under WIND on ICE without ever pressing a direction key.
at  60  shot 1_landed
at 180  shot 2_drifting
at 300  shot 3_sliding
at 420  shot 4_far_right
at 460  end

contact_sheet wind_ice cols 2 cell 960 540
